         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/7/90 ¶  ¶ In finishing the 8th decade of the Salsolaceae, ¶  dear Prof Tate, I come across your Bassia uniflora, gathered 11/6/83 at Lake Torrens. ¶  It is not the plant of RBr. (Sclerolaena uniflo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">90.07.18b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Ralph Tate</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Barr Smith Library, University of Adelaide, South Australia.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/7/90</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In finishing the 8th decade of the <name key="Salsolaceae">Salsolaceae</name>,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Part of B91.13.24.</p>
               </note> dear Prof Tate, I come across your <name key="Bassia%20uniflora">Bassia uniflora</name>, gathered 11/6/83 at Lake Torrens.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">SA.</p>
               </note> It is not the plant of RBr. (<name key="Sclerolaena%20uniflora">Sclerolaena uniflora</name>); but it may be a somewhat abnormal state of a Bassia, which among many others are on stone, but not yet printed off. It may however be a new species, and in that case I will dedicate it to you.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to R. Tate, 24 July 1890. M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bassia tatei</seg> in B90.09.02 and included it in B91.13.24 as plate LXXI.</p>
               </note> To settle this question, I should feel obliged, if you could send me soon, — if even on loan only, — more material, as I have only one small branchlet from you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bassia%20uniflora">Bassia uniflora</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Salsolaceae">Salsolaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sclerolaena%20uniflora">Sclerolaena uniflora</name>
            </p>
         </div>
